How to run demo:

##################################################
### AGL receiver side:

* Build and flash AGL branch dab_4.0.2.xml.

* Copy `SocketServer.py` and `receiver.py` to AGL board.

* Replace the contents of `/etc/xdg/weston.ini` on AGL with `NetworkDisplayDemo/weston.ini`.

* Restart weston to apply new config:
systemctl restart weston

* push required libs:
agl/src/build/tmp/work/aarch64-agl-linux/gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad/1.6.3-r0/image/usr/lib/gstreamer-1.0/libgstdebugutilsbad.so -> /usr/lib/gstreamer-1.0/libgstdebugutilsbad.so
agl/src/build/tmp/work/aarch64-agl-linux/gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad/1.6.3-r0/image/usr/lib/gstreamer-1.0/libgstivfparse.so -> /usr/lib/gstreamer-1.0/libgstivfparse.so

* Connect AGL to the same network with Android board and start receiver server:

./receiver.py

###################################################
### Ubuntu receiver side:

* Install gst-plugins-bad (exact package may vary):
sudo apt install gir1.2-gst-plugins-bad-1.0

* Start receiver:
./receiver.py

###################################################
### Android sender side:

* To be able to launch any activity on virtual display:

adb shell settings put global force_resizable_activities 1

* Ensure receiver.py is running on AGL and sender is in same subnet as receiver.

* Start castscreen on Android.

  - Start SenderApp on Android. (use ./open_cast_app.sh on host machine).
  - Wait for receiver to be shown in the list.
  - Select receiver.
  - Press 'Start'.
  - Use keyboard (Tab & Enter keys) to navigate through confirmation dialog.
  - Screencast should be running now.

* To cast google maps:

  # Launches Google Maps on virtual display
  # VIRTUAL_DISPLAY_ID is shown in Android application
  ./start_maps_virtual.sh [VIRTUAL_DISPLAY_ID]
